						<div class="postbody">There's been alot of talk that the IRQ counter decreases when the "A12 on the PPU bus toggles from 0-1".
<br />What does this mean in plain english? Does it mean when bit 12 of the PPU address switches from 0 to 1 when for example setting an address via $2006?
<br />It only decreases on toggle? Assuming the previous bit 12 was 1, and writing another 1 on bit 12 won't decrease the counter?
<br />
<br />Another question about $A001 register. It seems pretty simple but what's the point of disabling WRAM or make it readable/writable only? Is this feature actually used in games and if so, why? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

